  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine if the observed benefits of minimally invasive
      total knee arthroplasty, namely decreased hospital stay and increased range of motion, can be
      achieved with standard knee arthroplasty using the subvastus approach.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
